{"key":"processedPost-6704081","value":{"id":6704081,"first":6704024,"last":6704330,"when":1174698325,"utime":"03/24/07 04:05 AM","content":"Mushroom spores from the same species generally mate up without problem.  However, you don't know what you're getting, as it would still be multispore inoculation.  For a true cross with some assurance of potential, dikaryotic mycelium from isolated single sector proved fruiting strains can be crossed on agar, or individual monokaryons from single spores can be crossed, but the process is of course much trickier and requires a working knowledge of agar and microscopy.<br />RR","title":"Re: provenance versus cross breeding"}}